com.Cardinal.PermissionsPackage.Permissions

Interface IPredefinedSet


  • public interface IPredefinedSet
    Template for predefined permission sets. This is to only be used if you are planning on exporting a permission package. Include an instance of this in a IPermissionPackage interface.
    Author:
    Cardinal System

      • getSetLevel

        int getSetLevel()
        Gets the level of this set. NOTE: If this level matches an existing set or permission level, it will be changed.
        Returns:
        the level of this set. Returns -2 if this set is to be automatically assigned a level.
        See Also:
        PermissionRegistry.getUnusedLevel()
